The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               Pawar to head ICC committee
    Calcutta: The International Cricket Council (ICC) Sunday named Sharad Pawar, its president elect, as the chairman of the finance and commercial affairs committee, says A Staff Reporter. 
    BCCI president Shashank Manohar was named member of the governance review committee, according to an ICC news release.
    Pak players rsquo; appeal
    Karachi: Former Pakistan captains Ramiz Raja, Wasim Akram, Inzamam-ul Haq, Saeed Anwar and leg-spinner Mushtaq Ahmed have urged the government to stop sports minister Najamuddin Khan from representing the nation at the ICC executive board meeting this month.
    Nazar to quit
    Karachi: Former Pakistan Test opener Mudassar Nazar will quit as head coach of the National Cricket Academy in order to take up a coaching job at International Cricket Council rsquo;s (ICC) global cricket academy in Dubai.
    Akram view
    New Delhi: Former Pakistan captain Wasim Akram has termed the debate on the future of Indian cricket rsquo;s lsquo;fab four rsquo; meaningless, saying the quartet still has two years of international cricket left.
  ldquo;Agreed that the senior batsmen did not do well against Sri Lanka in the Test series but failure in one series cannot be the criteria to ask for a player rsquo;s omission, rdquo; he said.
    Jeev tied 33rd
    Kingsbarns: Milkha Singh faltered on the back nine to turn in a modest even-par 72 for a share of the 33rd spot after the penultimate round of the Alfred Dunhill Links golf Championship here. 
  The other Indians in fray Shiv Kapur (81) and Jyoti Randhawa (77) were at the tied 101st and 108th position respectively.
    Bhullar 43rd
    Seoul: Gaganjeet Bhullar brought home a card of one-over 72 to sign off tied 43rd, along with seven others, after the final round of the Kolon-Hana Bank Korea Open here Sunday.
    Hockey series
    Karachi: The Pakistan and Indian hockey federations have reached an agreement to revive bilateral Test series of their junior and senior teams in November and December.
  Pakistan Hockey Federation (PHF) secretary Asif Bajwa said the Indian junior team will visit Pakistan next month to play five Tests while their senior team will come in December for six matches.
    BHA AGM
    Calcutta: J.B. Roy was re-elected as the president of the Bengal Hockey Association (BHA) in its annual general meeting held on Saturday, says A Staff Reporter. Former Olympian Gurbux Singh was re-elected as the secretary. Sahara India remained the sponsors.
    THE OFFICE BEARERS:
    President: J.B. Roy; Vice-presidents: Surojit Purokaysta, Kumaresh Sen, Utpal Ganguly, Numi Mehta and Russi Jeejeebhoy; Secretary: Gurbux Singh; Treasurer: Gopinath Ghosh
                                                                                                                                                                 
